
---


@startuml

' Define Classes
class Doctor {
    +String fullName
    +String address
    +String phoneNumber
    +int practitionerNumber
    +Image signature
}

class Patient {
    +String firstName
    +String lastName
    +Date dateOfBirth
    +String address
    +String phoneNumber
    +String healthNumber
}

class Lab {
    +String name
    +String address
    +String registrationNumber
    +Time startTime
    +Time endTime
    +float cancellationFee
}

class Test {
    +String testName
    +Duration duration
    +TestGroup testGroup
    +boolean requiresAppointment
    +boolean allowsMultiple
}

class Requisition {
    +Date validFrom
    +Doctor doctor
    +Patient patient
    +List<Test> tests
    +Repetition repetition
}

class Appointment {
    +String confirmationNumber
    +Date appointmentDate
    +Time startTime
    +Time endTime
    +Lab lab
    +Requisition requisition
}

class Repetition {
    +int numberOfRepetitions
    +Interval interval
}

enum Interval {
    Weekly,
    Monthly,
    EveryHalfYear,
    Yearly
}

enum TestGroup {
    BloodTest,
    Ultrasound,
    XRay,
    UrineSample,
    StoolSample
}

' Relationships
Doctor "1" -- "0..*" Requisition : creates
Patient "1" -- "0..*" Requisition : is_patient_of
Patient "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : makes_appointment
Requisition "1" -- "1" Repetition : has_repetition
Requisition "1" -- "1..*" Test : includes_tests
Test "1" -- "1" TestGroup : belongs_to_group
Lab "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : provides_appointment_at
Appointment "1" -- "1" Requisition : for_requisition

' Constraints
note right of Requisition
  - A requisition can only include tests from the same group.
  - A doctor cannot be both prescriber and patient in the same requisition.
end note

note right of Appointment
  - Only one appointment can be made at a time for repeated tests.
  - Cancellation within 24 hours incurs a fee.
end note

@enduml

---

### 🔍 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Doctor**: Represents medical professionals who issue test requisitions. They must provide identification (practitioner number and digital signature).
- **Patient**: Individuals receiving tests. Must have a unique health number and personal details.
- **Lab**: A facility offering tests with specific business hours and fees.
- **Test**: A type of examination or test. Each test has a defined duration and may require an appointment.
- **Requisition**: A document issued by a doctor for one or more tests (of the same group). It also includes repetition rules.
- **Appointment**: A scheduled visit to a lab for a test. Patients can make/cancel appointments.
- **Repetition**: Defines how often a test should be repeated.
- **Enums**:
  - `Interval`: How frequently a test is repeated.
  - `TestGroup`: Used to categorize tests so they can be grouped on a single requisition.

